l; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; position: relative;\">\r\n<section class=\"mb10\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 10px !important 0px;\">\r\n<article class=\"article-content gtm-articleContent\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n<div id=\"articleimage\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 15px; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid #cccccc;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div id=\"artcontent\" class=\"artcontent roboto artbodytext\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"feed\" style=\"margin: 10px auto; padding: 0px; width: 640px; height: 360px; position: relative; display: inline-block; line-height: 27px !important;\"><img style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; height: auto; max-width: 100%;\" src=\"http://www.entrepreneur.com.ph//images/2017/07/31/20170728155136-GettyImages-518506642.jpeg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<div class=\"art-sns-feed-article\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; z-index: 2; cursor: pointer; bottom: 6px; right: 0px; position: absolute; opacity: 0.5;\">\r\n<div class=\"art-sns-feed-container\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; position: relative; font-size: 16px; height: 44px; width: 44px;\">\r\n<div class=\"art-sns-hex\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; transition: transform 350ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1) 350ms, opacity; z-index: 1; top: 0px; right: 0px; position: absolute; opacity: 1;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"art-sns-off\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">\r\n<div class=\"art-sns-count-container\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; width: 44px; height: 44px; vertical-align: middle; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"art-sns-count\" style=\"margin: 10px 0px 0px 48px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Source Sans Pro\', \'Trebuchet MS\';\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"art-sns-cancel\" style=\"margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; transition: transform 1s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1) 800ms; transform: scale(0) rotate(0deg); opacity: 0; right: 0px; top: 0px; height: 44px; position: absolute;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"art-sns-backdrop\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; transition: transform 350ms ease-out 300ms, visibility, opacity; visibility: hidden; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); color: #ffffff; opacity: 0; top: 0px; right: 0px; left: 0px; bottom: 0px; z-index: 1; position: absolute; font-size: 20px;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\" /><label class=\"image-content2\" style=\"margin: -15px 0px 5px 20px; padding: 0px; display: block; max-width: 100%; font-family: Arial; font-size: 10px; color: #999999; line-height: 30px;\">IMAGE istock / Getty Images Plus via Entrepreneur.com</label>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">Sometimes it doesn&rsquo;t feel like there&rsquo;s enough&nbsp;time&nbsp;in the day to get everything done. And for entrepreneurs and small-business owners, you&rsquo;re typically wearing a lot of hats and working long hours. So when it comes to completing non work-related tasks such as grocery shopping, cooking and cleaning, they can often fall to the bottom of your&nbsp;to-do list.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">Luckily today, with companies such as TaskRabbit and Uber, it&rsquo;s become easier to pay someone else to do these tasks for you and buy yourself more time to work on your business. It will cost you -- but it turns out many people are willing to pay. And that&rsquo;s a good thing, according to recent research.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">The&nbsp;study, published in the&nbsp;<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences</em>, found that people who spent money to save time were less stressed about how much time they had, and as a result, were&nbsp;happier.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">If you&rsquo;re stressed about drafting a pitch, coding your website or securing funding, doing small tasks such as grocery shopping and cleaning can sound like time-sucking nightmares. The good news is: outsourcing time-consuming tasks can not only give you the time to do what you do best, but keep you smiling.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">\"Money can buy happiness if you spend it right,\"&nbsp;said&nbsp;Elizabeth Dunn, University of British Columbia psychology professor and co-author of the study.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">In the study, researchers conducted a series of surveys with more than 6,000 people in the U.S., Denmark, Canada and the Netherlands to understand how a person\'s spending habits affects the way they feel. Overall, those who spent their money on things such as ordering takeout, taking a cab and hiring household help reported greater life satisfaction than those who spent their money on other things.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">As entrepreneurs, time is extremely valuable -- however, so is money. But the study found that whether a person was rich or poor, spending money on saving time boosted happiness levels. &ldquo;If there&rsquo;s some task that just thinking about it fills you with dread, then it&rsquo;s probably worth considering whether you can afford to buy your way out of it,&rdquo; Dunn said.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">So does that mean money can actually buy happiness?&nbsp;<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">No</em>. Buying new clothes, gadgets and other stuff doesn&rsquo;t in fact make you happier -- only buying time does. To test this, the researchers conducted another experiment where they provided participants $40 on two consecutive weekends and instructed them to spend the money on either material or timesaving purchases. Participants were asked their mood at the end of the day, and those who spent their money to save time were found to have less time-related stress and increased well-being. Material purchases did not have this effect.</p>\r\n<div class=\"ad-holder\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 15px 0px; height: auto;\">\r\n<div id=\"dynamic-ad-31\" class=\"dynamic-ad dynamic-ad-expand\" style=\"margin: 0px auto; padding: 10px 0px !important; visibility: visible; height: auto; text-align: center; background: #eeeeee; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10px; color: #999999; width: 640px; max-height: 250px; display: table; animation: weRecoInsertExpand 1s ease-in 0s backwards;\" data-id=\"31\">\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; height: 11px; display: table-row; line-height: normal !important;\">ADVERTISEMENT - CONTINUE READING BELOW&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div id=\"div-gpt-ad-1363694614885-31\" class=\"dfp_ad\" style=\"margin: 10px auto 0px; padding: 10px 0px 0px; display: table-cell; vertical-align: middle;\" data-google-query-id=\"CJ3pnOfGtdUCFYUAvAodFiYG8g\">\r\n<div id=\"google_ads_iframe_/1019353/entrepreneur_inview_run_and_grow_0__container__\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0pt none; display: inline-block; width: 300px; height: 250px;\"><iframe id=\"google_ads_iframe_/1019353/entrepreneur_inview_run_and_grow_0\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; border-width: 0px; border-style: initial; vertical-align: bottom;\" title=\"3rd party ad content\" src=\"http://tpc.googlesyndication.com/safeframe/1-0-9/html/container.html\" name=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"250\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" data-is-safeframe=\"true\"></iframe></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">Yet, whether you&rsquo;re a busy entrepreneur, an employee or a c-suite executive -- it&rsquo;s important to be mindful of the tasks you outsource or automate. While we have the resources to automate nearly everything today, doing tasks such as cooking and driving can help you build a diverse set of skills and give you opportunities to spend quality time with your significant other or family members.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">*****</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\"><em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Copyright &copy; 2017 Entrepreneur Media, Inc. All rights reserved.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 27px !important;\"><em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">This article originally appeared on&nbsp;</em><a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; color: #ff4200;\" href=\"https://www.entrepreneur.com/article/297931\">Entrepreneur.com</a><em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">. Minor edits have been done by the Entrepreneur.com.ph editors.</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</article>\r\n</section>\r\n</section>', NULL, NULL, '2017-07-31 23:52:37', '2017-07-31 23:52:37', '1'),
(4, 'Franchising', 'For Only Php208K, You Can Now Buy a Bakery Franchise from the Maker of Gardenia Bread', 'Popular bread manufacturer offers two franchise brands: Big Smile Bread Station and Bakersâ€™ Maison', 'uploads/banner_image/For Only Php208K, You Can Now Buy a Bakery Franchise from the Maker of Gardenia Bread.jpg', '<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">Since setting up shop in the country in 1997, Gardenia Bakeries Philippines Inc. has steadily built up its market footprint so that it now accounts for half of all the packed bread loaves sold in groceries and supermarkets. Almost always, Gardenia&rsquo;s loaves of bread, which are popular because they taste fresh longer, are sold out at the end of each day.</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">In search of sustained growth, the company, whose parent company is based in Singapore, made a big leap from bread making to direct retailing by building a chain of bakeries under a couple of brands: Big Smile Bread Station and Bakers&rsquo; Maison.</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">The two brands joined the Franchise Asia Expo last week at SMX Convention Center in Pasay City for the first time since its launch.</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&ldquo;We did market research and we found that for the unpacked breads industry, it has Php10 billion worth of potential,&rdquo; Gardenia&rsquo;s Franchise Development Supervisor Myra Nobleza told&nbsp;<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Entrepreneur Philippines</em>. &ldquo;At least 70 percent of that will come from community bakeshops, so that&rsquo;s the idea.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">Gardenia&rsquo;s Big Smile Bread Station has the look and feel of bakeshops found in small communities and barangays in the country. It sells traditional Filipino pastries such as&nbsp;<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">pan de coco</em>, ensaymada and even&nbsp;<em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">pandesal</em>&nbsp;to capture the mass market.</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">The company offers three store formats for the Big Smile bakery concept: six to nine-square-meter carts, nine to 12 square-meter-kiosks and full-scale stores that can be as large as 30 square meters. The cost of the franchise packages start at Php208,000 to as much as Php888,000.</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">Nobleza said Big Smile now has 41 company-owned branches and five franchised outlets across Luzon, mostly in NCR and in CALABARZON. The company wants to focus on these areas for now before expanding to the Visayas and Mindanao.</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&ldquo;We&rsquo;ve already made a name in the packed goods category so with these concepts, we hope to tap into the unpacked baked goods segment,&rdquo; Nobleza added. &ldquo;I think we&rsquo;re already at seventh place in terms of market share in the community bakeshops industry.&rdquo; Among its more well-known competitors are San Miguel Foods&rsquo; Kambal Pandesal and Julie&rsquo;s Bakeshop.</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">As for Bakers&rsquo; Maison, the upscale bakeshop brand aims to capture the middle-class market with a pastry selection more heavily influenced by international flavors. The brand, which originated in Australia, only has nine branches so far in Metro Manila, mostly found in malls. Gardenia previously said that it plans to have 100 branches in the near future.</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">Gardenia has enjoyed robust sales in the last six years. The company&rsquo;s net income more than doubled in 2015 to Php54.15 million from Php26.73 million in 2010, according to its financial statements submitted to the Securities and Exchange Commission.</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">The 21-year-old company is indirectly owned by Singapore-listed firm QAF Ltd., which operates Gardenia International.</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">*****</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"NoSpacing\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: \'Roboto Slab\', serif; font-size: 17px; line-height: 27px !important;\"><em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Elyssa Christine Lopez is a staff writer of Entrepreneur PH. Follow her on Twitter @elyssalopz</em>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, '2017-08-01 00:00:24', '2017-08-01 00:00:24', '1');
